# 10.0 Docs

> Documentation for 10.0 Docs.

- [Breaking change: BackgroundService runs all of ExecuteAsync as a Task](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/backgroundservice-executeasync-task.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where BackgroundService now runs the entirety of ExecuteAsync on a background thread instead of running the synchronous portion on the main thread.
- [Breaking change: Null values preserved in configuration](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/configuration-null-values-preserved.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where configuration providers now preserve null values instead of treating them as missing values.
- [Breaking change: Message no longer duplicated in Console log output](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/console-json-logging-duplicate-messages.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where `Message` is no longer duplicated in Console log output using the JSON formatter.
- [Breaking change: DynamicallyAccessedMembers annotation removed from trim-unsafe configuration APIs](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/dynamically-accessed-members-configuration.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where DynamicallyAccessedMembers annotations were removed from trim-unsafe Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration APIs.
- [Breaking change: Fix issues in GetKeyedService() and GetKeyedServices() with AnyKey](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/getkeyedservice-anykey.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where GetKeyedService() and GetKeyedServices() behavior changed when using KeyedService.AnyKey as the lookup key.
- [Breaking change: ProviderAliasAttribute moved to Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.Abstractions assembly](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/extensions/10.0/provideraliasattribute-moved-assembly.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 10 where the ProviderAliasAttribute class moved from the Microsoft.Extensions.Logging assembly to the Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.Abstractions assembly.
